    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-12-23T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-12-23T05:00:00-05:00" n="808"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d808">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.6363/300: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-23T19:00:00+09:00"
                            >December 23, 1936—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 23—9:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>266. Embassy’s 265, December 22, 8 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>My British colleague informs me that he has just received his instructions
                        to the effect that Eden agrees with your views and that Clive is to concert
                        with me and to proceed as soon as possible to joint representations to the
                        Japanese Government. Clive proposes that the two Embassies prepare an
                        identic memorandum to be communicated tomorrow, the 24th, to the Minister
                        for Foreign Affairs, either personally or in some other manner if the
                        Minister cannot see us.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Please rush instructions if not already sent. I feel that our
                        representations should be approximately simultaneous and substantially
                        identical not joint and identic.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>According to the telegram received by Clive, Eden also took advantage of
                        an interview with Yoshida<note n="93" xml:id="d808fn93">Shigeru Yoshida,
                            Japanese Ambassador in the United Kingdom.</note> to draw attention to
                        the difficult position of the British oil interests because of the failure
                        of the Japanese Government to live up to its promises.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
